  <section class="policy-section" id="service">
    <h2><span class="sec-num">2</span>Description of Service</h2>
    <p>Shield is a family internet protection platform that enables parents and guardians to manage and safeguard their children's online experience. The Service currently includes the following features:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>DNS Filtering:</strong> Blocks access to websites and online content in categories such as adult content, gambling, violence, phishing, and malware, using DNS-over-HTTPS (DoH) technology. Filtering applies on any network — home WiFi, school WiFi, and mobile 4G/5G data.</li>
      <li><strong>Parental Controls:</strong> Content category blocking, custom allow/block lists, internet schedule enforcement (e.g. no internet during school hours or after bedtime), and per-device screen time budgets.</li>
      <li><strong>Location Tracking:</strong> Real-time GPS location sharing for enrolled child devices, location history, and geofence alerts that notify parents when a child enters or leaves a designated area.</li>
      <li><strong>Alerts &amp; Notifications:</strong> Push notifications and optional messaging-app alerts (WhatsApp, Telegram) for key events such as blocked site attempts, geofence breaches, and SOS requests from a child.</li>
      <li><strong>Rewards System:</strong> A points-based incentive system allowing parents to assign tasks to children and reward compliance with screen time or other privileges.</li>
      <li><strong>Analytics &amp; Reporting:</strong> Summaries of browsing activity categories, time-online trends, and weekly digest emails.</li>
      <li><strong>ISP &amp; Multi-Tenant Deployment:</strong> White-label deployment for Internet Service Providers and enterprises to offer Shield as a managed service to their customers.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We reserve the right to modify, enhance, or discontinue any feature of the Service at any time with reasonable notice where practicable.</p>
  </section>

