    <p><strong>Accurate information:</strong> You agree to provide accurate, current, and complete information during registration and to keep your account information up to date. Providing false information may result in immediate suspension or termination of your account.</p>
    <p><strong>Account security:</strong> You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your account credentials and for all activity that occurs under your account. You must notify us immediately at <a href="mailto:legal@rstglobal.in">legal@rstglobal.in</a> if you suspect any unauthorised use of your account.</p>
    <p><strong>One account per household:</strong> A single parent account may manage multiple child profiles and devices. Sharing of parent account credentials with other adults who are not co-guardians of the enrolled children is not permitted.</p>
    <p><strong>ISP/Enterprise accounts:</strong> Organisations registering as Internet Service Providers or enterprises must provide valid business details. A designated administrator is responsible for compliance with these Terms across all sub-accounts provisioned under the organisation's tenant.</p>
