  <section class="policy-section" id="children">
    <h2><span class="sec-num">5</span>Children's Accounts</h2>
    <p>Shield is designed as a tool for parents and guardians to protect and manage their minor children's internet access. Child profiles and child device accounts are created by, and operate under the authority of, a registered parent or guardian account.</p>
    <p><strong>Parental responsibility:</strong> By creating a child profile, you confirm that you are the parent or legal guardian of that child and that you have the legal right to monitor their online activity and location. You take full responsibility for all data collected through child profiles associated with your account.</p>
    <p><strong>Transparency with children:</strong> We strongly encourage parents and guardians to be open with their children about the use of Shield. Age-appropriate transparency about internet filters, location sharing, and screen time rules promotes trust and digital literacy.</p>
    <p><strong>Data minimisation for children:</strong> We collect only the data necessary to provide the Service for child profiles. We do not use child data for advertising, profiling, or any purpose other than delivering and improving the parental control features. Please refer to our Privacy Policy for details.</p>
    <p><strong>No direct accounts for minors:</strong> Children under the age of 18 may not independently register for a Shield account. All access by minors is through child profiles administered by a parent or guardian.</p>
  </section>

