    <h2><span class="sec-num">6</span>Subscription &amp; Billing</h2>
    <p><strong>Free tier:</strong> Shield offers a free plan with core DNS filtering features. The features included in the free plan may change over time and are described on our pricing page.</p>
    <p><strong>Paid plans:</strong> Premium features are available through paid subscription plans billed monthly or annually. Prices are displayed in Indian Rupees (INR) inclusive of applicable taxes unless otherwise stated. ISP and enterprise plans are priced separately based on the number of managed customers.</p>
    <p><strong>Payment processing:</strong> All payments are processed securely through Stripe. By providing payment details, you authorise RST Global to charge your selected payment method on a recurring basis in accordance with your chosen plan. We do not store your full card details on our servers.</p>
    <p><strong>Renewals:</strong> Subscriptions renew automatically at the end of each billing cycle unless cancelled before the renewal date. You will receive a reminder email before each renewal.</p>
    <p><strong>Cancellation:</strong> You may cancel your subscription at any time from the Shield dashboard. Cancellation takes effect at the end of the current billing period. You will retain access to paid features until that date. No partial-period refunds are issued unless required by applicable law.</p>
    <p><strong>Refunds:</strong> If you believe you have been charged in error, please contact us at <a href="mailto:legal@rstglobal.in">legal@rstglobal.in</a> within 14 days of the charge. We review refund requests on a case-by-case basis.</p>
    <p><strong>Price changes:</strong> We may update subscription prices with at least 30 days' notice before the change takes effect. Continued use of the Service after a price change constitutes acceptance of the new pricing.</p>
    <p><strong>Taxes:</strong> You are responsible for all applicable taxes. Where required by law, RST Global will collect GST or other taxes at the point of payment.</p>
  </section>

